/* 1050 -- mig2 cost arm: SovVal-as-CIC, the over-K type-level lift (H6 / M13).
 * An over-budget SovVal must FAIL to type-check.  p5_kat_mig2_lek (numera/typecheck.iii):
 *   LeK(c) = Id(Bool, LEK(c,budget), true); LEK(cost_slot, budget_slot) iota-reduces (in the CCL
 *   kernel reducer) to TRUE iff cl_le_product(cost, budget) over the full CL_DIM=6 cost vector
 *   (NOT a scalar compromise).  Within-budget: refl:LeK type-checks.  Over-budget (dim 0 = 20 > 10):
 *   LEK => FALSE, so Id(Bool,FALSE,TRUE) is uninhabited -> REJECTED -- over-K lifted from runtime
 *   SV_STATUS_REFUSED to a TYPE error, the kernel VERIFYING the budget by iota. 99 = both arms. */
module corpus_1050
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn p5_kat_mig2_lek() -> u64 from "typecheck.iii"
fn main() -> u64 { return p5_kat_mig2_lek() }
